[[File:Pike Place Magic Shop Pike Place Market Seattle Washington.JPG|thumb|A magic shop in [[Seattle]], displaying posters of famous magicians and also advertising "gags"]]

A '''magic store''' (also '''magic shop''' or '''magician's supply shop''') is an establishment which sells materials for performing [[magic trick]]s. Magic shops often also sell [[practical joke]]s and [[novelty item]]s, and frequently serve as informal gathering places for amateur magicians, with some hosting organized [[magic club]]s.<ref name=idiots>{{cite book |title=The Complete Idiot's Guide to Magic Tricks |first=Tom |last=Ogden |publisher=Penguin |year=1998 |isbn=9780028627076 |pages=333–334 |accessdate=November 7, 2012 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=GdEuf2YJ2SEC&pg=PA334&dq=magic+shops&hl=en&sa=X&ei=RcmbUPOAOrO1yQG7-oCABQ&ved=0CEgQ6AEwBjgK#v=onepage&q=magic%20shops&f=false}}</ref>

