===Humans===
====1st & 2nd Series====
;{{nihongo|Nozomu Hanamura|花村 望|Hanamura Nozomu}}	
:{{animevoices|[[Natsuki Hanae]]<ref name="crunchy"/>}}	
:The main human protagonist of season 1, he is a kind and gentle 12-year-old (13 in season 2) middle school student who is searching for the Fairilu's existence after his grandmother gave him a picture book about them. Apart from the first episode, he has never had any direct contact with them until episode 55, when he finally meet Lip again.
:In season 3, he appears as a Fairilu named '''Drop'''. Like his human self, he is in love with Lip.
;{{nihongo|Karen Hanamura|花村 かれん|Hanamura Karen}}
:{{animevoices|[[Mamiko Noto]]}}
:Nozomu's younger sister, she debuts in and is the main human protagonist of season 2. She was in hospital of a foreign country when she discovered Rin's Fairilu Seed, which seemed to give her encouragement, and she cherished it. Later in Little Fairilu, where Rin's seed was brought back in order to let her born into the world, she encouraged Rin to open the Door of Birth and finally, Rin succeeded.

====3rd Series====
;{{nihongo|Arisu Hanazono|花園 ありす|Hanazono Arisu}}
:{{animevoices|[[Emiri Iwai]]}}
:The main human protangonist of season 3, she is a middle school student who is always worried. Being a transfer student and not good at talking with others, she cannot make friends easily. One day she discovered Magical Pendulum and a magic book in a grocery store, which made her meet Lip and Spica and went to Little Fairilu with them.

==Media==

===Merchandise===
The franchise was first announced in Press Conference on December 11, 2015 as the second collaboration work between [[Sanrio]] and [[Sega Sammy Holdings]], meant for the younger female demographic. It was revealed also that the series will have themes relating to flowers and keys, as well as [[mermaid]]s and insects with characters officially based on the said themes.<ref name="prtimes">{{cite web|url=http://prtimes.jp/main/html/rd/p/000000161.000001909.html|title=セガトイズ、サンリオ共同キャラクタープロジェクト第2弾！新キャラクター「リルリルフェアリル」が誕生。小学生女児にむけて商品化、ＴＶアニメ化決定！|publisher=}}</ref> Merchandise of the series is officially planned, including stationary, toys, raincoats, clothing and more and was released in March 2016. In games, the series will appear in the next installment of the [[Apron of Magic]] Arcade game.<ref name="animatetv">{{Cite news
|date=2015-12-11|url=http://www.animate.tv/news/details.php?id=1449822786|title=「ジュエルペット」に続く、セガトイズ×サンリオ共同開発プロジェクト「リルリルフェアリル」が発表! TVアニメ化も!?|publisher=アニメイトラボ|work=[[アニメイトTV]]|accessdate=2015-12-12}}</ref><ref>{{cite tweet |author=  |user= maho_ap|number= 675228438450585600 |date= 11 Dec 2015 |title= にしむらシェフ：魔法のエプロン公式 Twitter 2015年12月11日 17:19の発言 |access-date=  }}</ref> More information of the franchise was unveiled on the 2016 Sanrio Expo on January 30, 2016, which includes the [[Sanrio Puroland]] Mascot form of Lip as well as revealed merchandise.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://getnews.jp/archives/1373306|title=【SANRIO EXPO2016】『セガトイズ』×『サンリオ』共同企画第2弾　アニメ『リルリルフェアリル』が2月6日放送開始！ ｜ ガジェット通信|date=30 January 2016|publisher=}}</ref>

===Anime===
An anime adaptation of the series, titled {{nihongo|'''''Rilu Rilu Fairilu ~ Yousei no Door ~'''''|リルリルフェアリル～妖精のドア～|Riru Riru Feariru ~ Yōsei no doa ~|"Rilu Rilu Fairilu ~ The Fairy's Door ~"|lead=yes}} is officially animated by [[Studio DEEN]] and began airing in all [[TX Network|TXN]] stations in Japan on February 6, 2016, replacing ''[[Jewelpet: Magical Change|Jewelpet Magical Change: Dream Selection]]'' on its initial timeslot, and is ended in March 25, 2017. It is directed by [[Sakura Gojō]] and written by [[Aya Matsui]] (''[[Boys Over Flowers]]'', ''[[Marmalade Boy]]'', ''[[Tamagotchi! (anime)|Tamagotchi!]]'').<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2015-12-24/sanrio-sega-toys-rilu-rilu-fairilu-tv-anime-premieres-on-february-6/.96902|title=Sanrio, Sega Toys' Rilu Rilu Fairilu TV Anime Premieres on February 6|publisher=}}</ref> The anime's opening theme is titled '''Brand New Days''' by [[Korean Pop]] group [[Apink]] as their 5th Japanese Single.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://kpopfighting.com/2016/02/02/a-pink-to-release-brand-new-days-japanese-single-in-march/|title=A pink to release ‘Brand New Days’ Japanese single in March|first=|last=Alvin|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.musicman-net.com/artist/53961.html|title=Apink、初の日本オリジナル楽曲「Brand New Days」がアニメ『リルリルフェアリル』主題歌に - Musicman-NET|publisher=}}</ref> The first ending theme is titled '''key of life''' by Shiggy Jr,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.universal-music.co.jp/shiggyjr/news/2016/01/29|title=未発表楽曲｢key of life｣がテレビ東京系アニメ｢リルリルフェアリル～妖精のドア～｣エンディング曲に決定!!|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://natalie.mu/music/news/174212|title=Shiggy Jr.、アニメ「リルリルフェアリル」ED曲担当|first=Natasha,|last=Inc.|publisher=}}</ref> the second is titled {{nihongo|'''Kera Kera Acchi Muite Hoi!'''|ケラケラあっちむいてホイ!||"Kera Kera Face that Way!"|lead=yes}} by [[Kera Kera]], and the third is titled {{nihongo|'''Rilu Rilu Wonderful Girl!'''|りるりるわんだふるがーる！|Riru Riru Wandafuru Gāru!|lead=yes}} by [[Yumiri Hanamori]], [[Rina Hidaka]], [[Aya Uchida]] and [[Aina Kusuda]] as Lip, Sumire, Himawari and Rose.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://prtimes.jp/main/html/rd/p/000000111.000016719.html|title=『リルリルフェアリル～妖精のドア～』EDテーマ『りるりるわんだふるがーる！』CD本日発売♪|publisher=}}</ref>

A sequel, titled {{nihongo|'''''Rilu Rilu Fairilu ~ Mahou no Kagami ~'''''|リルリルフェアリル～魔法の鏡～|Riru Riru Feariru ~ Mahō no kagami ~|"Rilu Rilu Fairilu ~ The Magic Mirror ~"|lead=yes}} was announced by Sanrio via the official Anime [[Twitter]] account,<ref>{{cite tweet |author=アニメ「リルリルフェアリル」公式 |user= rilurilu_anime|number= 831684116303142913|date= 15 Feb 2017 |title= Tweet announcing the new series|access-date= 2017-06-28 }}</ref><ref name="Anime News Network"/> began airing on April 7, 2017, and is set to end on March 30, 2018. It is directed by Sakura Gojō and [[Nana Imanaka]], written by [[Akemi Omode]]. The first opening theme of this series is titled {{nihongo|'''Papipupe Pon!'''|ぱぴぷぺPON!|lead=yes}} by Girl group Apink as their 7th Japanese Single together with their song "Bye Bye",<ref>{{cite web|url=https://ameblo.jp/apink-japan/entry-12252607378.html|title=「ぱぴぷぺPON！」が『リルリルフェアリル〜魔法の鏡〜』のオープニングテーマ曲に決定！|publisher= |date=2017-03-02|accessdate=2017-06-28}}</ref> and the second is titled {{nihongo|'''Sakura Saku Aoi Haru'''|さくら咲く青い春||"Sakura Blooming Blue Spring"|lead=yes}} by [[Silent Siren]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://natalie.mu/music/news/262875|title=SILENT SIREN新曲がアニメ「リルリルフェアリル」OPテーマに|publisher= |date=2017-12-26|accessdate=2017-12-27}}</ref> The first ending theme is titled {{nihongo|'''Onegai Roji'''|お願いロジー|lead=yes}} by [[Q-pitch]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://q-pitch.com/news/166/|title=「【『お願いロジー』がテレビ東京系アニメ「リルリルフェアリル～魔法の鏡～」エンディングテーマ曲に決定！！】|publisher= |date= |accessdate=2017-06-28}}</ref> and the second is titled {{nihongo|'''Fairy Smile'''|フェアリースマイル|Fearī Sumairu|lead=yes}} by the same group.<ref>{{cite tweet |author=|user= qpitch_sibtv|number= 913695203612966913|date= 29 Sep 2017 |title= Tweet announcing the new ending theme of the second anime|access-date= 2017-09-30 }}</ref>

A third season, titled {{nihongo|'''''Oshiete Mahou no Pendulum ~ Rilu Rilu Fairilu ~'''''|おしえて魔法のペンデュラム～リルリルフェアリル～|Oshiete mahō no penduramu ~ Riru Riru Feariru ~ |"Tell Me, Magical Pendulum ~ Rilu Rilu Fairilu ~"|lead=yes}} began its airing on [[Kids Station]], [[Animax]] and [[Tokyo MX]], and the premiere dates are July 7, July 8 and July 15, 2018 respectively.<ref name="thirdseason" /> It is directed by [[Chisei Maeda]] and written by Akemi Omode. The anime's opening theme is titled {{nihongo|'''Oshiete Mahou no Pendulum'''|おしえて魔法のペンデュラム||"Tell Me, Magical Pendulum"|lead=yes}} by Yumiri Hanamori and [[Ari Ozawa]] as Lip and Spica. The ending theme is titled {{nihongo|'''"Suki" no Katachi'''|"好き"のカタチ||"Shape of Love"|lead=yes}} by Yumiri Hanamori as Lip.

